{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"57450174-f3b1-430e-859d-52412173b57f","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9 opt-in bridge and is **no longer needed**.\n\nYou can safely remove it:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_hGUtyALar2H88SF82aogoV","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_Ma1Tq78qgmiIduEj3Xxvmn","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-e4b0b8523be548778a380642d633d4d1/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-e4b0b8523be548778a380642d633d4d1/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"5395735d-f2fd-4dfa-b1ab-18e54f610956","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about MTP support. Let me explain what changed in .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed because MTP integration is built-in. In fact, in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses MTP by default.\n\nKey changes for .NET 10:\n1. `dotnet test` uses MTP natively - no need for `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`\n\n\n2. `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required to make the test project an executable that runs on MTP\n3. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was essentially a workaround for .NET 9 to enable MTP with `dotnet test`, but since it's now the default in .NET 10, they can safely remove it from their project file.","outputTokens":562,"requestId":"E3F7:1A0B9E:163F839:18E16BF:6A052095"},"id":"309d4a44-05f9-4598-8e6e-f114f78f25d5","timestamp":"2026-05-